{% extends 'base.html.twig' %}

{% block title %}Anishinaabemowin · OIATC{% endblock %}
{% block description %}OIATC's flagship language program: one fluent speaker's recorded teachings becoming a living course, with a curated corpus now, Lesson 1 in prototype, language games returning at relaunch, and a talking doll in design, on technology the community controls.{% endblock %}
{% block og_title %}Anishinaabemowin{% endblock %}
{% block og_description %}One fluent speaker's recorded teachings becoming a living course: a curated corpus now, Lesson 1 in prototype, language games returning at relaunch, and a talking doll in design.{% endblock %}
{% block body_class %}route-anishinaabemowin{% endblock %}

{% block head_styles %}{% include 'partials/funder-styles.html.twig' %}
  <style>
    /* Page-scoped, on the site tokens (light/dark aware): the Lesson 1 word taste
       (text only, no image boxes) and the Minoo funnel CTA. */
    .lang-sublabel { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 11px; letter-spacing: 0.1em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--accent-deep); margin: var(--gap-5) 0 0; }
    .lang-taste { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr); gap: var(--gap-3); margin: var(--gap-3) 0 0; }
    @media (max-width: 640px) { .lang-taste { grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); } }
    .lang-tcard { background: var(--paper-2); border: 1px solid var(--rule); border-left: 3px solid var(--accent-soft); border-radius: var(--radius-md); padding: 14px 16px; }
    .lang-tcard__word { font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: 20px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--ink); line-height: 1.2; }
    .lang-tcard__en { font-size: 13.5px; color: var(--ink-3); margin-top: 4px; }
    .lang-note { font-size: 12.5px; color: var(--ink-3); line-height: 1.55; margin: var(--gap-3) 0 0; max-width: 80ch; }
    .lang-minoo { background: var(--accent-wash); border: 1px solid var(--accent-soft); border-left: 4px solid var(--accent); border-radius: var(--radius-lg); padding: 20px 22px; margin: var(--gap-5) 0 0; display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; align-items: center; gap: 14px; justify-content: space-between; }
    .lang-minoo p { margin: 0; color: var(--ink); font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.55; max-width: 54ch; }
    .lang-minoo__btn { display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 9px; font-family: var(--font-sans); font-size: 15px; font-weight: 600; border-radius: 999px; padding: 10px 20px; text-decoration: none; white-space: nowrap; }
    .lang-minoo__btn--live { color: var(--paper); background: var(--accent-deep); }
    .lang-minoo__btn--live:hover { filter: brightness(1.08); }
    .lang-minoo__btn--soon { color: var(--ink-2); background: var(--paper-3); border: 1px dashed var(--rule-strong); cursor: default; }
  </style>
{% endblock %}

{% block content %}
{# Minoo is the destination platform where the lessons actually run. It is being
   relaunched on community infrastructure (DNS still propagating), so the CTA is a
   "relaunching soon" placeholder. To go live: set minoo_relaunching to false (the
   live URL is already wired). Tracked in PROGRESS.md. #}
{% set minoo_relaunching = true %}
{% set minoo_url = 'https://minoo.live' %}
<article class="fund-wrap fund-wrap--narrow">

  <p class="fund-eyebrow">OIATC program · Flagship</p>
  <h1>Anishinaabemowin</h1>
  <p class="fund-lede">One fluent speaker's recorded teachings, becoming a living course on technology the community controls.</p>

  <div class="fund-body">
    <p><a href="https://www.facebook.com/profile.php?id=61582894730998" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Steven Bennett</a> shares his teachings of Anishinaabemowin publicly. Lesson 1 is built from them, with his agreement: everyday kitchen words, each with the Anishinaabemowin as he writes it and the English beside it. The program records one fluent speaker's teachings, builds low-pressure places to hear the language, and builds learning tools the community controls. The 2021 Census put the average age of the Ojibway mother-tongue population at 48, so the next twenty years decide whether transmission restarts or ends.</p>
  </div>

  <p class="lang-sublabel">A taste of Lesson 1: the kitchen</p>
  <div class="lang-taste">
    <div class="lang-tcard"><div class="lang-tcard__word">dboosk-naagan</div><div class="lang-tcard__en">bowl</div></div>
    <div class="lang-tcard"><div class="lang-tcard__word">Emkwaan</div><div class="lang-tcard__en">spoon</div></div>
    <div class="lang-tcard"><div class="lang-tcard__word">mookman</div><div class="lang-tcard__en">knife</div></div>
    <div class="lang-tcard"><div class="lang-tcard__word">Doopwin</div><div class="lang-tcard__en">table</div></div>
  </div>
  <p class="lang-note">Spelling is shown exactly as Steven writes it. The full lesson, with audio and a practice mode that hides the English, runs on Minoo.</p>

  <section class="fund-sec">
    <h2>The work, by stage</h2>
    <ul class="fund-links">
      <li><span class="fund-stage fund-stage--live">Live</span> The curated corpus <span>· 27 items from one fluent speaker's teachings, consent-tracked</span></li>
      <li><span class="fund-stage fund-stage--proto">Prototype</span> Lesson 1 <span>· kitchen vocabulary, 16 items; goes live on Minoo at relaunch</span></li>
      <li><span class="fund-stage fund-stage--proto">Prototype</span> The language games <span>· Shkoda, Matcher, Agim, a crossword, and Minoo's Journey; built, on Minoo, returning at relaunch</span></li>
      <li><span class="fund-stage fund-stage--idea">Idea</span> <a href="/anishinaabemowin/doll">The talking doll</a> <span>· a fluent Elder's voice in a child's hands, offline; in design</span></li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="fund-sec">
    <h2>How it is made</h2>
    <div class="fund-body">
      <p>The fluent speaker records. The corpus is curated by hand. It is built into lessons. And it runs on infrastructure the community controls, not a platform that can be switched off from outside. That is OIATC's <a href="/positions/sovereign-ai">position on AI sovereignty</a>, applied to a language: the data and the ground a community owns are the parts that last.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="lang-minoo">
    <p>The full lesson, with audio and practice mode, lives on Minoo, the community platform where you actually learn the language.</p>
    {% if minoo_relaunching %}
    <span class="lang-minoo__btn lang-minoo__btn--soon" aria-disabled="true">Learn it on Minoo · relaunching soon</span>
    {% else %}
    <a class="lang-minoo__btn lang-minoo__btn--live" href="{{ minoo_url }}" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Learn it on Minoo &rarr;</a>
    {% endif %}
  </div>

  <section class="fund-sec">
    <h2>The fundable next step</h2>
    <div class="fund-body">
      <p>Funding extends the corpus beyond one speaker, ships the next lessons end to end, and pilots the doll batch and a season of community story nights. The <a href="/support">Support page</a> carries the specific asks.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="fund-more">
    <p class="fund-more__k">More from this program</p>
    <div class="fund-more__links">
      <a href="/anishinaabemowin/doll">The talking doll</a>
      <a href="/programs/anishinaabemowin">Funding summary</a>
      <a href="/programs">All programs</a>
      <a href="/support">Support this program</a>
    </div>
  </div>

</article>
{% endblock %}
